c","position":{"commit_sha":"9529dcb2f6f306a0021fab30a527ed422675d4c8","position":"1784239786625877001-4bbbdff5-65f5-40d4-ac40-4a05eebe1a9c"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"faef351493322a547932452d7d35015899bc17c34ee31fd2d081b577a9fe1639","event_uuid":"426ce700-2f98-4846-a10c-b9e8a7f02455","position":{"commit_sha":"acff59c5f7ae95d33a507074a3999f8e61a3e658","position":"1784240244190124001-426ce700-2f98-4846-a10c-b9e8a7f02455"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"0b3239190c6c372b7f530e51c09b8707c10f2ab6be4328933d3496f238f77162","event_uuid":"16d46092-46c9-43b0-8ca4-6eb823bb46e3","position":{"commit_sha":"2dd7c19563afba0d699877ae77d59263c217e09d","position":"1784241222701882974-16d46092-46c9-43b0-8ca4-6eb823bb46e3"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-211_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"dd03eb60-2371-4b50-91b1-9fd0c63ef175","comments":[],"created_at":1784238925251530001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"860a9884-afc4-4b82-b2d1-44cef232b550","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"c8ed-d52d-0c75-4b51"}],"description":"## Why\nBug c8ed (outbound depends_on link direction) shipped because the link-sync tests exercised\nthe relation vocabulary with a single representative (`blocks`, ~19×; `depends_on` 0×), used\nmechanical stub assertions, and the only semantic round-trip oracle\n(`tests/external/test_link_sync_roundtrip_live.py`) is gated behind live Jira. An audit found\nthree OTHER gaps of the same shape, all in the link-sync seam.\n\n## What\nClose the sibling gaps by PARAMETRIZING the link tests over the FULL relation vocabulary, so\nevery current AND future relation is covered (no more single-representative blind spots).\nTest-only change; no production behavior changes.\n\n## Scope\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_dedup.py`: parametrize outbound `_diff_links`\n  emission over ALL relations — assert `(jira_type, swap)` for each MAPPED relation\n  (blocks→Blocks/False, depends_on→Blocks/True, relates_to→Relates/False) and assert `[]` for\n  each UNMAPPED/skip relation (duplicates, supersedes, discovered_from). [Findings 1 + 3]\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_removal_sync.py`: add a REMOVE case where a\n  Jira issue carries an OUTWARD `Blocks` link whose local `depends_on` dep was removed; assert\n  the emitted mutation is `{action: remove, relation: depends_on}` (the untested branch of the\n  REMOVE path's own inward/outward direction logic at outbound_links.py:193-202). [Finding 2]\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] An outbound emission test is parametrized over all 6 relations: the 3 mapped ones assert\n  the exact `(type, swap)` tuple; the 3 unmapped ones assert an empty mutation list.\n  Proof: `.venv/bin/pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_dedup.py -q`.\n- [ ] A REMOVE test covers outward-`Blocks`→`depends_on`. Proof:\n  `.venv/bin/pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_removal_sync.py -q`.\n- [ ] The new cases assert per-relation ORIENTATION, not mere presence: the `depends_on` emission\n  case asserts `swap is True`, and the applier case asserts the SWAPPED endpoint tuple — so a\n  re-drop of the c8ed swap fix would fail them (a real guard, not a tautology). Proof:\n  `.venv/bin/pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_dedup.py tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_link_sync.py -q` is green.\n- [ ] `make lint`/`make typecheck` pass; no production source files change.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_dedup.py","reason":"parametrize outbound emission over full relation vocabulary (mapped type/swap + unmapped skip)"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/diffing/test_link_removal_sync.py","reason":"cover outward-Blocks->depends_on REMOVE branch"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"10ad97d9-c97f-4989-b94c-980623a60060","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"bb82-30bf-e235-4b09","ticket_type":"task","title":"Harden link-sync tests: parametrize over the full relation vocabulary (close the c8ed test-gap class)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["69134a5d-9714-48fc-922b-4c0b70b10fd4","860a9884-afc4-4b82-b2d1-44cef232b550","7ec85e43-b11a-4ef7-ac93-466aeae99cd6","5cbc52d5-0720-4602-8c9f-980e1da436e1","4bbbdff5-65f5-40d4-ac40-4a05eebe1a9c","426ce700-2f98-4846-a10c-b9e8a7f02455","10ad97d9-c97f-4989-b94c-980623a60060","4a199b7e-f8ce-461f-aea8-d39ddc888cf0","16d46092-46c9-43b0-8ca4-6eb823bb46e3"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784241222701882975,"uuid":"09b929f8-a523-4d61-8b86-2a468bb61486"}